    Deputy Minister of Police Bongani Mkgonki and Western Cape Community Safety MEC in a tense stand-off at Nyanga Police Station. Video: Jason Felix/Cape Argus.
   
   
    
   
  
 
 
  Maimane then went to the front of the Nyanga police station, but he was doorstopped by some ANC supporters.
 
 
  
 
 
  “If he wants to come and talk to me, he can come. Otherwise I will get him at Parliament,” Maimane said.
 
 
  
 
 
  When the DA’s march reached the Nyanga Police station, there was a group protesting for housing. The groups were separated by police fearing clashes.
 
 
  
 
 
  
   







